cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with a problem in which candidates are distributed into queues and the employer wants to hire multiple candidates among the best ones. This problem involves data structures (cs.DS) and game theory (cs.GT) as the protocol needs to make decisions based on the behavior of the candidates. The paper also proposes an optimal deterministic protocol, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT) to optimize the decision-making process. Finally, the paper provides theoretical analysis of the problem, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) to understand the performance of the protocol.
